The paper discusses the performance of the standard stochastic gradient descent (SGD) algorithm in learning neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the algorithm. Additionally, the paper's focus on the expressivity of neural networks and their ability to learn various functions suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational intelligence (cs.SI).
